==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|hybernate}} {{qualifier|obsolete}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|hibernātus}}, from {{m|la|hibernō}}, from {{m|la|hībernus||winter}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈhaɪbəˌneɪt/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|hibernat}}

# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To spend [[winter]] time in [[hibernation]].
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To live in [[seclusion]].
# {{lb|en|intransitive|computing}} To enter a [[standby]] state which conserves power without losing the contents of [[memory]].
#* '''2001''', Microsoft Corp, ''Use Hibernate and Standby to Conserve Batteries''
#*: Your computer '''hibernates''' after it has been idle for the specified amount of time.

